# CC PROMPT — v2.31.4 — feat(ops): deathstar-backup.sh — atomic backup with key fingerprint

## What this does
A one-shot backup helper that always captures the three things needed to restore
DEATHSTAR from scratch:

1. Full Postgres dump (`pg_dump -Fc`)
2. `/opt/hp1-agent/docker/.env` (contains `SETTINGS_ENCRYPTION_KEY`)
3. The current key fingerprint (verified against `/api/status/health/crypto`),
   written next to the dump so a restorer can prove the `.env` matches the dump
   BEFORE attempting a restart.

All three go into a single timestamped bundle. If `age` is installed, the bundle
is encrypted at rest with a recipient pubkey; otherwise the `.env` inside the
bundle is left in plaintext and the bundle tar is chmod 600.

Also adds a companion `deathstar-verify-bundle.sh` that validates a bundle
without restoring — reads the stored fingerprint, re-derives the one from the
bundled `.env`, and reports match/mismatch. Cheap insurance.

Two new files under `scripts/`. No API changes. No container restart needed.

Version bump: v2.31.3 → v2.31.4

